                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/12–2844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-28T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 28, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 29—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>194. I desire to thank the Department for the information conveyed in its No. 151
                    of December 27, 1 p.m.<note n="75" xml:id="d186fn75">Not printed; it informed
                        Ambassador MacVeagh of President Roosevelt’s telegram No. 673, December 13,
                        to Prime Minister Churchill, <ref target="#pg_150">p. 150</ref>.</note> just
                    received. Mr. Churchill has left Athens, and I greatly regret that my long
                    conversation with him yesterday (see my 190, of December 27, 7 p.m. for the
                    President) had to be carried on without my knowledge of this important
                    background.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
